        <div n="818B200L" type="letter"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-818B200L-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-818B200L-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-818B200L-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-818B200L-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-818B200L-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-818B200L-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-818B200L-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-818B200L-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-818B200L-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="verse-paragraph"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-818B200L-line-1"> Dear Dick prithee tell by what passion you move&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-818B200L-line-2"> The World is in doubt whether Malice or Love;</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-818B200L-line-3"> And while at good Cashel you rail w<hi rend="sup">th</hi></l></lg><lg n="2" type="verse-paragraph"><l n="4" xml:id="spp-818B200L-line-4"> such spite&#13;</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-818B200L-line-5"> They shrew'dly suspect it is all but a bite.</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-818B200L-line-6"> You certainly know tho' so loudly you vapour</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-818B200L-line-7"> His Spite cannot wound who attempted the Draper.</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-818B200L-line-8"> Then prithee reflect, take a word of advice</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-818B200L-line-9"> And as your old wont is, change hands in a trice.</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-818B200L-line-10"> On his Virtues hold forth, 'tis your very best way,</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-818B200L-line-11"> And say of the man, what all honest men say;</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-818B200L-line-12"> But if yet obdurate your Anger remains</l><l n="13" xml:id="spp-818B200L-line-13"> And still your foul bosom more rancor contains,</l><l n="14" xml:id="spp-818B200L-line-14"> Say then more than they say, nay lavishly flatter</l><l n="15" xml:id="spp-818B200L-line-15"> Tis your gross panegericks alone can bespatter.</l><l n="16" xml:id="spp-818B200L-line-16"> For you my dear Dick, give me leave to speak plain</l><l n="17" xml:id="spp-818B200L-line-17"> Like a very foul Mop, dirty more than you clean.818B200L   </l></lg></div>
      </div>
